      <h2 id="faq">FAQ</h2>
      
      <h3>How does symbolic verification work?</h3>
      <p>Skyla uses a combination of symbolic rules and semantic processing to determine state transitions. Each transition is recorded with a cryptographic proof that can be independently verified.</p>
      
      <h3>What makes Skyla different from other AI agents?</h3>
      <p>Skyla provides cryptographic guarantees about agent behavior through zero-knowledge proofs. Every decision and state change can be verified without revealing sensitive internal information.</p>
      
      <h3>Can I audit agent decisions?</h3>
      <p>Yes, all agent state transitions include proofs that can be independently verified. The symbolic imprint and proof envelopes provide complete transparency into agent reasoning.</p>
      
      <h3>Is the system production-ready?</h3>
      <p>Skyla is currently in alpha development. The core verification mechanisms are functional, but the API and tooling are still being refined for production use.</p>
